        "timestamp": "2018-12-24 06:35:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nLogback is used on WAR-level, Tomcat on the other hand has separate logging configuration. If we want to mute Tomcat we need to provide separate config for container-level logs. So I just added to default config lines 66-72 which effectively exclude console handler for given packages. All other stuff is already in base tomcat image under /usr/local/tomcat/conf/logging.properties. I could append these lines to config directly via `echo` but I thought it would be confusing.\n\nAbout changing log level, not sure where you spot that change, which line bring you to that conclusion?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
